original_title: Bronx: Tremont Avenue (East - White Plains Road
text:
View 1: East Tremont Avenue at the north-west cor. White Plains Road, Bronx, showing the White Plains Road bridge over the New Haven Railroad tracks.
View 2: White Plains Road and East Tremont Avenue, north-east corner, showing the Unionport Road bridge over the tracks. The gasoline station occupies a triangular plot between the two thoroughfares.

Sept. 4, 1939
P. L. Sperr, photographer

original_title: Bronx: White Plains Road - Tremont Avenue (East)
text:
(view 1) White Plains Road at East Tremont Avenue, looking southeastward and showing construction of the Parkchester Houses, on the former site of the Catholic Protectory.

(view 2) White Plains Road and Westchester Avenue, Bronx, looking southeastward and showing construction of the Parkchester Houses.

(view 3) Castle Hill Avenue at St. Raymond Avenue, Bronx, looking northwestward and showing construction of Parkchester Houses.

(view 4) Castle Hill Avenue, opposite Glover Street, Bronx, looking northwestward and showing construction of the Parkchester Houses.

P. L. Sperr, photographer
September 4, 1939
